>JD: AEEOSSY 2H .AY +20 373
#note I spent what can only be described as an unhealthy amount of time analyzing this pre-endgame! 3 in the bag is tough, especially since it's beyond what Quackle can solve analytically. The TL;DR is that I should empty the bag here on purpose. First of all, I need to block the top of the board because of the threat of HABANERO (whenever a bingo is in the bag natural AND there's a blank, there's a much higher chance opponent has it). From there, I essentially lose when Anand bingos, and win when he does not (I can score enough with OSES at G12). If I leave a tile in the bag with HAY, however, I give Anand a chance to fish into an unblockable bingo combination - either AENORT?, in which case he has STONERAW/ANORETIC, or ABENOR? in which case he has JAWBONER at top and BANDEROL/BANNEROL at bottom-left. In summary, I should block the top and empty the bag, for roughly an 81% win chance, versus 73% after my play of HAY (please don't ask me how I got these percentages).
>Anand_Buddhev: ABNORTV 1J BARTON +34 364
#note as it turns out, I'm lucky and Anand can't fish for one of the danger racks of AENORT? or ABEORT?.
